    "We order them as per task complexities based on measurement across four complexity dimensions that are leveraged from the work by Liu and Li (2012).",
    "The seven tasks along with example task prompts (for nationality demographic) are presented in Figure 2.",
    "Defining task complexity has been a challenging endeavor since long back in history (Klir and Simon, 1991).",
    "Multiple studies have shown the significant effects of task complexity but there is no universally accepted framework for defining task complexities (Liu and Li, 2012).",
    "Campbell (1988) first attempted to provide an objective definition of task complexity."
